A Tanzanian pastor was detained on Monday for fraudulently obtaining more than Sh1.5 million from a Kenyan businessperson.Eustace Mutasingwa, who is also a businessman, is said to have obtained the money from Loy Mbati by pretending he could import a vehicle for her.Senior principle magistrate Martha Mutuku granted the investigating officer permission to continue detaining the suspect as the matter in probed.In a miscellaneous application, police detective Bernard Asirigwa said the probe would require him to go to Mombasa to confirm details of the case.Mutasingwa was arrested on September 24 at his residence within Nairobi.The case will be mentioned on October 3 for plea taking.